msContents.summary: This Antiphonal was produced in Tuscany (likely Pisa) in the second quarter of the fourteenth century. It contains material from the Temporale and Sanctorale for Septuagesima and the Pre-Lenten season. It contains three large historiated initials by an artist working in a style close to that of Francesco Traini. The miniatures depict King David playing the psaltery before God (f. 21), the Martyrdom of Saint Agnes (f. 146), and the Martyrdom of Saint Agatha (f. 257).

supportDesc.extent: i+145+i; 626 x 435 mm bound to 650 x 470 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Later pagination in ink, arabic numerals, outer margins; 1-182, 185-222, 225-294 (fols. 92, 112 missing)

layoutDesc.layout: Five four-line staves ruled in red with square notation and text in black; frame-ruled in lead with double vertical bounding lines; written area: 450 x 295 mm

decoDesc.decoNote: Three historiated initials, two lines (two staves plus their underlying text) in height (King David playing the psaltery before Jesus, p. 21; Martyrdom of Saint Agnes, p. 146; Martyrdom of Saint Agatha, p.257); numerous decorated initials one line (one staff plus its underlying text) in height, in orange, yellow, pink, and green with white dots on blue ground, some with acanthus marginal extensions, one at the beginning of each chant, up to three on a page; rubrication in red
21Inhabited initial D, King David before God
[21 miniature]Inhabited initial D, King David before God
146Historiated initial D, Martyrdom of Saint Agatha
[146 miniature]Historiated initial D, Martyrdom of Saint Agatha
257Historiated initial O, Martyrdom of Saint Agatha; Illuminated initial, Letter A
[257 miniature]Historiated initial O, Martyrdom of Saint Agatha; Illuminated initial, Letter A

binding.p: Original fifteenth-century leather over wooden boards with five metal bosses each on front and back cover
